---
title: Truffled Sirloin Steak Ramen with Mushrooms, Bok Choy & Sesame Seeds
description: Indulge in a decadent bowl of ramen topped with juicy sirloin steak and elevated with earthy truffle seasoning. Mushrooms, garlic, and scallions flavor a rich broth in which springy noodles and crisp bok choy and napa cabbage cook to perfection. Truffle butter adds more rich flavor, and a shower of nutty sesame seeds tops it all off!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6863be390203e9f8dbb4c6ee-a28d46c8.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6863be390203e9f8dbb4c6ee-en-US.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 51 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 2550 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/truffled-sirloin-steak-ramen-6863be390203e9f8dbb4c6ee
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{8%oz}(trimmed and sliced) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced, whites and greens separated).

Pat @sirloin steak{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until beginning to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in garlic and scallion whites. Cook, stirring frequently, until veggies are tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir half the @soy sauce{2%tbsp} (all for 4 servings) into pot with veggies. Cook, stirring, until liquid is mostly evaporated, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in 4 cups water (7 1⁄2 cups for 4), @mushroom stock concentrate{2} and @pork ramen stock concentrate{2}.

Bring to a boil, then add @ramen noodles{4.5%oz}. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Add @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%oz} and @black truffle butter{2%tbsp}. Stir until butter has melted and veggies are wilted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide noodles and broth between #bowls{}. Fan steak over top. Garnish with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Sprinkle with @truffle seasoning{2%g} to taste. Serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.